.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH dreamd 1  "dreamd " 
.SH NAME
dreamd \- Portable memory layer for AI coding agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdreamd\fR [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Portable memory layer for AI coding agents
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version information
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
dreamd\-doctor(1)
Run health checks and print status (dream\-cycle mode, etc.)
.TP
dreamd\-dream(1)
Run the deterministic dream cycle: promote top cluster to LESSONS.md, prune decayed episodic events
.TP
dreamd\-init(1)
Scaffold per\-project .agent/ store and register it with the daemon
.TP
dreamd\-mcp(1)
Start the MCP server (bridges to daemon if running, otherwise in\-process)
.TP
dreamd\-reset(1)
Reset scratch state (DR\-113). Today only `workspace` is supported
.TP
dreamd\-watch(1)
Run the daemon in foreground mode. Blocks until SIGINT/SIGTERM
.TP
dreamd\-version(1)
Print structured version information (semver, commit, build date, target, schema)
.TP
dreamd\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
